article.headline: Tennessee Tech 68, Austin Peay 65
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Kevin Murphy had 18 points and hit the game-winning 3-pointer with 6 seconds left to give Tennessee Tech a 68-65 win over Austin Peay on Tuesday night in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference tournament. The Golden Eagles (15-16), seeded sixth, rallied from an eight-point deficit with 13:09 left and led the third-seeded Governors 56-51 with 6:09 to go. Austin Peay (17-15) pulled ahead 57-56, then Tennessee Tech regained the lead on a layup by Alfred Jones, who also scored 18 points. Anthony Campbell's 3-pointer with 8 seconds left made it 65-65, then Murphy hit his decisive shot to send the Golden Eagles into a semifinal game Friday against Morehead State, which defeated Jacksonville State 87-54. Tennessee Tech shot 65.5 percent (19-for-29) in the second half while the Governors shot 61.9 percent (13-for-21). Campbell scored 16 to lead Austin Peay.
